condolence /kənˈdəʊləns/

(condolences) 

1. N-UNCOUNT A message of condolence is a message in which you express your sympathy for someone because one of their friends or relatives has died recently. 吊唁 

例： Neil sent him a letter of condolence. 尼尔给他发了一封吊唁信。 

2. N-PLURAL When you offer or express your condolences to someone, you express your sympathy for them because one of their friends or relatives has died recently. 哀悼 

例： He expressed his condolences to the families of the people who died in the incident. 他向那次事故遇难者家属表达了哀悼。

</div>

